schema.description: The test event of FULL TWAMP.

twamp-result.description: The test result of FULL TWAMP.

connection-id.description: The connection ID,the upper limit of this parameter depend on the device.

connection-id.description: The connection ID,the upper limit of this parameter depend on the device.

server-port.description: The port number of server,ranges from 1025 to 65535,or 862.

vrf-name.description: The VRF name,the length of this string is from 1 to 32.

retry-count.description: The connection retry count,ranges from 0 to 16(default:10).

retry-interval.description: The connection retry interval,ranges from 10s to 900s(default:30s).

session-id.description: The session ID,the upper limit of this parameter depend on the device.

sender-port.description: The port number of sender,ranges from 1025 to 65535,or 862.

receiver-port.description: The port number of receiver,ranges from 1025 to 65535,or 862.

vrf-name.description: The VRF name,the length of this string is from 1 to 32.

detect-path.description: Detect path type,including down and up(default:down).

dscp.description: The DSCP value of packet,ranges from 0 to 63(default:0).

padding-length.description: The length of padding,the upper limit of this parameter depends on the device.(default:27bytes).

time-out.description: Timeout ranges from 1s to 10s(default:5s).Within this time,the server needs to reflect the test message, otherwise the message is discarded.

report-interval.description: If it is assigned, it will upsend the result in interval of configured value. Otherwise, it does not upsend until it is stopped.

continuous.description: Continuous sending packet mode.In this mode,the test packets will always be sent until the user stops.
Continuous sending packet mode.In this mode,the test packets will always be sent until the user stops.

packets.description: The mode of sending packet according to the number of configuration.In this mode,the test will be stopped until the number of sending packet reaches the configured value.

send-count.description: The number of sending packet,ranges from 1 to 65535.The test will be stopped until the number of sending packet reaches the configured value.

seconds.description: The mode of sending packet according to the configuration of time.In this mode,the test will be stopped until the time of sending packet reaches the configured value.

send-time.description: Sending time of packets,the value of this parameter ranges from 60s to 86400s.The test will be stopped until the time of sending packets reaches the configured value.

delay-statistics-mode.description: The delay statistics mode,including bidirection,unidirection and both, the default of this parameter depend on the device.

proactive-status.description: The proactive status,including start and stop.

operation.description: The proactive operation type,including start and stop.

server-status.description: The status of TWAMP server,including enable and disable(default:disable).

max-connection-duration.description: The maximum duration of connection,ranges from 0h to 24h(default:0).If this node is assigned 0,it means permanence connection unless stopped manually.If it is assigned 1h to 24h,it means connection lasting time.

max-connections.description: The maximum number of connections,the minimum value of this parameter is 1,the maximum value of this parameter depends on the device(default:64).

max-sessions.description: The maximum number of sessions,the minimum value of this parameter is 1,the maximum value of this parameter depends on the device(default:128).

max-sessions-per-connection.description: The maximum session number of every connection,the minimum value of this parameter is 1,the maximum value of this parameter depends on the device(default:8).

port.description: The port number of server,ranges from 1025 to 65535,or 862(default:862).

ignore-vrf.description: The ignore-vrf status,including enable and disable(default value depend on the device).

list-status.description: The status of client list,including enable and disable(default:disable).
